<font color="#FF0000">RE: FROM ANOTHER VIET-AMERICAN</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jun  6 13:08:04 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Dear Lien,<br><br>
As a Vietnamese American like yourself, I would like to tell you this.  It's not important what others think of us but what of think of ourself.  We are a group of people that have every right to be in this nation just a others do.  We should be proud of ourself that within the last 22 years, we made the most out of this dream land than any other group of refugees.  We have been classified by many experts and organizations to be the most sucessful group of refegee people in the last three decades.  Unlike others who have been here for hundred of years, we have just been here for only 22 years.  Most of us are recent arrivals.  Within 22 years, we produced more than 255,000 college graduates.  Half of this are post graduates like yourself and I.  We turned dead town into thriving business center.  We set up our own shops...and much more.<br><br>
For most American that I came to know with, they are very support and proud of us.  But for some, our big house, nice car...really  sore their eyes.  What they didn't know is that we came to this country with only a few plastic bags on our hands.  We worked days and nights for it.  The mentality among our Vietnamese Americans are...if we dared to crossed that Indian Ocean with tiny wooden boats, If we dared to crossed the Cambodia and Thai jungles to reach to the refegee camps...then nothing is going to stop us making the best out of this God given land.<br><br>
Just remember....like the Jews, they are being hated by many because they are good at what they do.  They own and run too many shops, banks etc...This made a lot of people afraid of them taking over.  This's one of the reason Adolf Hitler killed so many of them.  We must look at the American Jews and follow their foot steps.  Let no barrier prevent us from being the best.<br><br>
We owe American for our life and happiness.  We should always be the best we can be.
<p><code>--   (Vietson) </code><p>


